content.description: Small boulder in bottom below tiggers tree house very featured.
content.location: There are three defined lines on this boulder, none are that hard but all three are fun! left to right Roo v0 Rue v0 And Ruex v0

content.description: Low crux, fun soft pockets! Big awesome side pull!!
content.location: Starts on Low soft pockets to the right of the crack, Moves up onto two edges and then a big reach to the big side pull hueco and up onto edges over the top!

content.description: Fun tall move between good cripms!
content.location: Same Start as Kite left but traverses right under the "Kite" feature on under clings, and follows under cling and crimps up and over the top

content.description: Good Holds and fun movement, low crux
content.location: Starts 12 feet to the right of Christopher Robin, On a left hand pocket and right hand on a good edge, climbs left of the "Kite" feature on the wall and up good pockets and edges of the top

content.description: Low Crux On long moves through Big holds!! Perfect Height to be fun spooky!!
content.location: This Route Starts On a Good rail On the Cliff band Where the burned dead tree has fallen off the cliff, From Rail move up and left to a good sidepull/undercling Then big moves up big holds to a tall slabby top out with good holds!!

content.description: Crux is sticking a high foot halfway up Amazing movement and holds!! Mega classic
content.location: located 15 feet past little red wagon Starts on the obvious hueco pocket and follows two low dishes into a deep two finger pocket, then up good dishes on the face to a high foot move into a deep jug and then long reaches between good holds over the top!

content.description: Slopey climbing to a crux hop to big jug on arête.
content.location: This is the first prominent arête on the Tiggers tree house cliff band, Starts matched in the hueco pocket and follows slopey arête and pinches to a jump move to the big jug on the arête, then straight up over the top!

content.description: Exposed move to a good flake high on the face
content.location: This Line starts same as eeyore's arête but traverses right on good pinches and edges around bulge to slopy dish, then up prow on good edges to a slopey pinch and exposed move to a flake and then over the top!
